You can report the facts on the  <a href="http://www.leonarddevinci.signalement.net">www.leonarddevinci.signalement.net</a> platform, and an appointment with the VSS referents will be proposed to you shortly.

In addition, you can contact the health referent or the de Vinci Higher Education listening cell : on-campus on Thursday afternoons, or with Pros-Consulte by video, chat or telephone.

Si vous rencontrez un dysfonctionnement sur l'application mobile, vous devez utiliser le portail web <a href="https://www.leonard-de-vinci.net/">www.leonard-de-vinci.net.</a>

Vous pouvez également envoyer une demande d'aide pour signaler le problème.

&nbsp;

The<strong> "Modify submitted work"</strong> feature in DVL allows students to submit a new version of their work. Simply click on <strong>"Edit submision"</strong> next to the original submission, load the new version and click on "Save changes".

The teacher also has this feature and can modify a student's submitted work when viewing the submitted work by clicking on <strong>"View all submissions"</strong> then next to the work to be modified click on <strong>"Edit" &gt; "Edit submission".</strong>

